Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced into half moons). Peel the @carrot{1}(peeled and sliced into thin half moons) and remove the top and bottom, then cut in half lengthways and slice into thin half moons. Slice the @chestnut mushrooms{1}(sliced). Trim the tops from the @green beans{1}(trimmed and chopped into four pieces) and chop them and the @baby corn{1}(chopped into four pieces) into four pieces.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium heat. Add the onion, carrot and mushrooms. Cook, stirring frequently, until everything has softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir the @tomato puree{1%30g}, @Goan Xacuti curry powder{1.5}, @tamarind sauce{1/2} (only use the amount stated in the ingredient list!) and half the @ground turmeric{1/2} into the veggies. Cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add the @coconut milk{400%ml}, half the @vegetable stock pot{1} and bring to a simmer. Cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the remaining turmeric and stock pot into another large saucepan with the @water{300%ml} (amount specified in the ingredient list). Bring to the boil on high heat, stir to dissolve the stock pot and add the @basmati rice{150%g}. Lower the heat to medium and cover with a #lid{} on (or some foil). Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes}.

> The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Once the curry has simmered away for 10 mins, add the green beans and baby corn. Continue to cook until the beans are tender, another ~{8-10%minutes}. Taste and add @salt{} and @black pepper{} if necessary.

Place the @salted peanuts{25%g} between two sheets of #clingfilm{}. Bash them with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a saucepan.

Fluff the rice up with a fork and spoon it into #bowls{}. Top with the veggie curry and sprinkle over the peanuts. Enjoy!